com.sri.ai.grinder.sgdpllt.core.solver

Class AbstractSGVET

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.grinder.sgdpllt.core.solver.AbstractMultiQuantifierEliminator
      • com.sri.ai.grinder.sgdpllt.core.solver.AbstractSGVET
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MultiIndexQuantifierEliminator
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SGVET

    public class AbstractSGVET
extends AbstractMultiIndexQuantifierEliminator
    A MultiIndexQuantifierEliminator generalizing the Variable Elimination algorithm in the same manner DefaultMultiIndexQuantifierEliminator is generalized from DPLL, that is, it can produce symbolic answers and it does not need to only solve problems with the operations from its classic version (for the case of VE, sum and product, or max and product).

    It relies on a partial decomposition of the problem, producing instances to be solved by a SGDPLL(T) solver, in the following manner: 

     sum_{i1,...,i_n} prod_j f_j(args_j)
 =
 sum_{i1,...,i_{n-1}} prod_{j : args_j does *not* contain i_n} f_j(args_j) sum_{i_n} prod_{j : args_j contains i_n} f_j(args_j)
    and then solving 
     sum_{i_n} prod_{j : args_j contains i_n} f_j(args_j)
    with DefaultMultiIndexQuantifierEliminator. Note that the symbolic capability of SGDPLL(T) is crucial here, as args_j for the various functions f_j will typically involve other indices which, at the level of the sub-problem, are free variables.
    Author:
    braz
